{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-01",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_01_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "01 - Proem & Down the Rabbit-hole",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.699,
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 3,
  "page_start_sec": 243.6,
  "page_end_sec": 484.82,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 243.6,
      "end": 245.0,
      "text": "She took down a jar from one of the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 245.06,
      "end": 246.06,
      "text": "shelves as she passed it."
    },
    {
      "start": 246.14,
      "end": 247.88,
      "text": "It was labeled Orange Marmalade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.96,
      "end": 249.44,
      "text": "but to her disappointment it was empty."
    },
    {
      "start": 250.34,
      "end": 251.9,
      "text": "She did not like to drop the jar for",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 251.9,
      "end": 253.16,
      "text": "fear of killing somebody underneath,"
    },
    {
      "start": 253.6,
      "end": 256.42,
      "text": "so managed to put it into one of the cupboards as she fell past it."
    },
    {
      "start": 257.87,
      "end": 258.42,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 258.58,
      "end": 259.44,
      "text": "thought Alice to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 259.74,
      "end": 261.36,
      "text": "after such a fall as this I shall"
    },
    {
      "start": 261.36,
      "end": 262.58,
      "text": "think nothing of tumbling downstairs."
    },
    {
      "start": 263.44,
      "end": 265.18,
      "text": "How brave they'll all think of me at home.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 265.52,
      "end": 265.68,
      "text": "Why,"
    },
    {
      "start": 265.72,
      "end": 267.06,
      "text": "I wouldn't say anything about it even"
    },
    {
      "start": 267.06,
      "end": 268.56,
      "text": "if I fell off the top of the house,"
    },
    {
      "start": 269.08,
      "end": 270.12,
      "text": "which was very likely true."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.14,
      "end": 271.9,
      "text": "Down,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 272.04,
      "end": 272.42,
      "text": "down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.48,
      "end": 272.72,
      "text": "down."
    },
    {
      "start": 273.76,
      "end": 275.36,
      "text": "Would the fall never come to an end?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 276.26,
      "end": 278.42,
      "text": "I wonder how many miles I've fallen by this time,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 278.52,
      "end": 278.96,
      "text": "she said aloud."
    },
    {
      "start": 279.2,
      "end": 281.62,
      "text": "I must be getting somewhere near the center of the earth."
    },
    {
      "start": 281.82,
      "end": 282.8,
      "text": "Let me see,"
    },
    {
      "start": 282.92,
      "end": 284.0,
      "text": "that would be four thousand"
    },
    {
      "start": 284.18,
      "end": 284.74,
      "text": "miles down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 284.86,
      "end": 285.18,
      "text": "I think."
    },
    {
      "start": 285.82,
      "end": 286.18,
      "text": "For you see,"
    },
    {
      "start": 286.26,
      "end": 288.8,
      "text": "Alice had learned several things of this sort in her lessons in the"
    },
    {
      "start": 288.84,
      "end": 289.18,
      "text": "schoolroom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 289.32,
      "end": 290.78,
      "text": "and though this was not a very good"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.78,
      "end": 292.48,
      "text": "opportunity for showing off her knowledge,"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.68,
      "end": 292.94,
      "text": "as"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.94,
      "end": 294.1,
      "text": "there was no one to listen to her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 294.56,
      "end": 296.28,
      "text": "still it was good practice to say it over."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.5,
      "end": 297.1,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 297.14,
      "end": 297.54,
      "text": "that's about"
    },
    {
      "start": 297.54,
      "end": 298.16,
      "text": "the right distance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 298.34,
      "end": 301.18,
      "text": "but then I wonder what latitude or longitude I've got to."
    },
    {
      "start": 301.52,
      "end": 303.16,
      "text": "Alice had no idea what"
    },
    {
      "start": 303.32,
      "end": 303.96,
      "text": "latitude was,"
    },
    {
      "start": 304.06,
      "end": 305.02,
      "text": "or longitude either,"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.54,
      "end": 307.6,
      "text": "but thought they were nice grand words to say."
    },
    {
      "start": 308.992,
      "end": 309.48,
      "text": "Presently she",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 309.58,
      "end": 310.08,
      "text": "began again."
    },
    {
      "start": 310.36,
      "end": 312.64,
      "text": "I wonder if I shall fall right through the earth."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.18,
      "end": 314.26,
      "text": "How funny it'll seem to come"
    },
    {
      "start": 314.26,
      "end": 316.42,
      "text": "out among the people that walk with their heads downwards."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.8,
      "end": 317.78,
      "text": "The antipathies,"
    },
    {
      "start": 317.84,
      "end": 318.16,
      "text": "I think."
    },
    {
      "start": 319.28,
      "end": 319.86,
      "text": "She was rather",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 319.92,
      "end": 321.82,
      "text": "glad there was no one listening this time,"
    },
    {
      "start": 321.9,
      "end": 323.44,
      "text": "as it didn't sound at all the right word."
    },
    {
      "start": 324.16,
      "end": 324.48,
      "text": "But I shall",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 324.48,
      "end": 326.48,
      "text": "have to ask them what the name of the country is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 326.56,
      "end": 326.8,
      "text": "you know."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.05,
      "end": 327.5,
      "text": "Please,"
    },
    {
      "start": 327.54,
      "end": 327.84,
      "text": "ma'am,"
    },
    {
      "start": 327.86,
      "end": 328.86,
      "text": "is this New Zealand or"
    },
    {
      "start": 328.98,
      "end": 329.26,
      "text": "Australia."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.6,
      "end": 331.62,
      "text": "And she tried to curtsy as she spoke,"
    },
    {
      "start": 331.82,
      "end": 334.02,
      "text": "fancy curtsying as you're falling through the air."
    },
    {
      "start": 334.44,
      "end": 335.48,
      "text": "Do you think you could manage it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.86,
      "end": 338.84,
      "text": "And what an ignorant little girl she'll think me.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 339.4,
      "end": 339.68,
      "text": "No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 339.84,
      "end": 340.8,
      "text": "it'll never do to ask."
    },
    {
      "start": 341.02,
      "end": 342.78,
      "text": "Perhaps I shall see it written up somewhere."
    },
    {
      "start": 344.05,
      "end": 344.7,
      "text": "Down,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 344.94,
      "end": 345.34,
      "text": "down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 345.4,
      "end": 345.66,
      "text": "down."
    },
    {
      "start": 346.28,
      "end": 347.68,
      "text": "There was nothing else to do,"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.8,
      "end": 349.66,
      "text": "so Alice soon began talking again."
    },
    {
      "start": 350.784,
      "end": 352.22,
      "text": "Dinah will miss me very much tonight,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 352.34,
      "end": 352.88,
      "text": "I should think."
    },
    {
      "start": 353.2,
      "end": 354.14,
      "text": "Dinah was the cat."
    },
    {
      "start": 354.68,
      "end": 355.74,
      "text": "I hope they'll remember"
    },
    {
      "start": 355.96,
      "end": 357.42,
      "text": "her saucer of milk at tea-time."
    },
    {
      "start": 358.0,
      "end": 358.5,
      "text": "Dinah,"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.5,
      "end": 358.78,
      "text": "my dear,"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.88,
      "end": 360.14,
      "text": "I wish you were here down with me."
    },
    {
      "start": 360.72,
      "end": 361.06,
      "text": "There are no"
    },
    {
      "start": 361.1,
      "end": 361.7,
      "text": "mice in the air,"
    },
    {
      "start": 361.8,
      "end": 362.12,
      "text": "I'm afraid,"
    },
    {
      "start": 362.2,
      "end": 363.18,
      "text": "but you might catch a bat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 363.34,
      "end": 364.58,
      "text": "and that's very like a mouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 364.66,
      "end": 364.9,
      "text": "you know."
    },
    {
      "start": 365.72,
      "end": 366.68,
      "text": "But do cats eat bats,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 366.82,
      "end": 367.12,
      "text": "I wonder?"
    },
    {
      "start": 367.86,
      "end": 370.4,
      "text": "And here Alice began to get rather sleepy and went on saying",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 370.4,
      "end": 370.74,
      "text": "to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 371.0,
      "end": 372.1,
      "text": "in a dreamy sort of way,"
    },
    {
      "start": 372.3,
      "end": 373.7,
      "text": "Do cats eat bats?"
    },
    {
      "start": 373.96,
      "end": 375.32,
      "text": "Do cats eat bats?"
    },
    {
      "start": 375.44,
      "end": 376.22,
      "text": "And sometimes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 377.1,
      "end": 377.98,
      "text": "Do bats eat cats?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 378.2,
      "end": 379.02,
      "text": "For you see,"
    },
    {
      "start": 379.12,
      "end": 380.58,
      "text": "as she couldn't answer either question,"
    },
    {
      "start": 380.72,
      "end": 381.58,
      "text": "it didn't much matter"
    },
    {
      "start": 381.82,
      "end": 382.6,
      "text": "which way she put it."
    },
    {
      "start": 383.34,
      "end": 384.7,
      "text": "She felt that she was dozing off,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 384.84,
      "end": 386.32,
      "text": "and had just begun to dream that"
    },
    {
      "start": 386.32,
      "end": 388.14,
      "text": "she was walking hand in hand with Dinah,"
    },
    {
      "start": 388.22,
      "end": 389.7,
      "text": "and saying to her very earnestly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 389.88,
      "end": 390.92,
      "text": "Now Dinah,"
    },
    {
      "start": 390.92,
      "end": 391.12,
      "text": "tell"
    },
    {
      "start": 391.12,
      "end": 391.62,
      "text": "me the truth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 392.06,
      "end": 392.98,
      "text": "did you ever eat a bat?"
    },
    {
      "start": 393.56,
      "end": 394.06,
      "text": "When suddenly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 394.26,
      "end": 394.58,
      "text": "thump,"
    },
    {
      "start": 394.78,
      "end": 395.5,
      "text": "thump,"
    },
    {
      "start": 396.32,
      "end": 397.36,
      "text": "down she came upon a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 397.36,
      "end": 398.76,
      "text": "heap of sticks and dry leaves,"
    },
    {
      "start": 398.94,
      "end": 400.0,
      "text": "and the fall was over."
    },
    {
      "start": 401.408,
      "end": 402.44,
      "text": "Alice was not a bit hurt,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 402.58,
      "end": 403.34,
      "text": "and she jumped"
    },
    {
      "start": 403.48,
      "end": 404.58,
      "text": "up onto her feet in a moment."
    },
    {
      "start": 405.14,
      "end": 405.64,
      "text": "She looked up,"
    },
    {
      "start": 405.7,
      "end": 407.06,
      "text": "but it was all dark overhead."
    },
    {
      "start": 407.34,
      "end": 408.56,
      "text": "Before her was another"
    },
    {
      "start": 408.76,
      "end": 409.28,
      "text": "long passage,"
    },
    {
      "start": 409.48,
      "end": 411.06,
      "text": "and the white rabbit was still in sight,"
    },
    {
      "start": 411.2,
      "end": 412.04,
      "text": "hurrying down it."
    },
    {
      "start": 412.8,
      "end": 413.48,
      "text": "There was not a moment",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 413.48,
      "end": 413.96,
      "text": "to be lost."
    },
    {
      "start": 414.24,
      "end": 415.9,
      "text": "Away went Alice like the wind,"
    },
    {
      "start": 416.06,
      "end": 417.64,
      "text": "and was just in time to hear it say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 417.82,
      "end": 418.78,
      "text": "as it turned a corner,"
    },
    {
      "start": 419.2,
      "end": 419.36,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 419.48,
      "end": 420.42,
      "text": "my ears and whiskers,"
    },
    {
      "start": 420.44,
      "end": 421.24,
      "text": "how late it's getting!"
    },
    {
      "start": 422.2,
      "end": 424.06,
      "text": "She was close behind it when she turned the corner,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 424.2,
      "end": 426.04,
      "text": "but the rabbit was no longer to be seen."
    },
    {
      "start": 426.78,
      "end": 427.98,
      "text": "She found herself in a long,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 428.1,
      "end": 429.68,
      "text": "low hall which was lit up by a"
    },
    {
      "start": 429.68,
      "end": 431.26,
      "text": "row of lamps hanging from the roof."
    },
    {
      "start": 432.28,
      "end": 433.98,
      "text": "There were doors all around the hall,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 434.18,
      "end": 434.84,
      "text": "but they were all"
    },
    {
      "start": 435.06,
      "end": 435.36,
      "text": "locked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 435.76,
      "end": 438.9,
      "text": "and when Alice had been all the way down one side and up the other,"
    },
    {
      "start": 439.04,
      "end": 440.02,
      "text": "trying every door,"
    },
    {
      "start": 440.22,
      "end": 441.92,
      "text": "she walked sadly down the middle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.04,
      "end": 443.98,
      "text": "wondering how she was ever to get out again."
    },
    {
      "start": 445.12,
      "end": 445.86,
      "text": "Suddenly she came",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 445.96,
      "end": 447.6,
      "text": "upon a little three-legged table,"
    },
    {
      "start": 447.78,
      "end": 449.04,
      "text": "all made of solid glass."
    },
    {
      "start": 449.36,
      "end": 451.0,
      "text": "There was nothing on it but a tiny"
    },
    {
      "start": 451.1,
      "end": 451.7,
      "text": "golden key,"
    },
    {
      "start": 451.86,
      "end": 453.88,
      "text": "and Alice's first idea was that this might"
    },
    {
      "start": 453.88,
      "end": 455.5,
      "text": "belong to one of the doors of the hall,"
    },
    {
      "start": 456.04,
      "end": 456.6,
      "text": "but alas,"
    },
    {
      "start": 456.62,
      "end": 459.26,
      "text": "either the locks were too large or the key was too small,"
    },
    {
      "start": 459.8,
      "end": 460.76,
      "text": "but at any rate it would not"
    },
    {
      "start": 460.94,
      "end": 461.68,
      "text": "open any of them."
    },
    {
      "start": 461.92,
      "end": 462.74,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 462.96,
      "end": 463.86,
      "text": "on the second time around,"
    },
    {
      "start": 464.04,
      "end": 465.98,
      "text": "she came upon a low curtain she had not"
    },
    {
      "start": 465.98,
      "end": 466.6,
      "text": "noticed before,"
    },
    {
      "start": 466.94,
      "end": 469.86,
      "text": "and behind it was a little door about fifteen inches high."
    },
    {
      "start": 470.16,
      "end": 471.18,
      "text": "She tried the little"
    },
    {
      "start": 471.26,
      "end": 472.26,
      "text": "golden key in the lock,"
    },
    {
      "start": 472.4,
      "end": 473.82,
      "text": "and to her great delight it fitted."
    },
    {
      "start": 476.032,
      "end": 477.6,
      "text": "Alice opened the door and found that",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 477.6,
      "end": 478.86,
      "text": "it led into a small passage,"
    },
    {
      "start": 479.08,
      "end": 480.58,
      "text": "not much larger than a rat hole."
    },
    {
      "start": 480.78,
      "end": 482.5,
      "text": "She knelt down and looked along the"
    },
    {
      "start": 482.54,
      "end": 484.82,
      "text": "passage into the loveliest garden you ever saw."
    }
  ]
}